ut the effectiveness of my favorite (and main) class in EQ, especially when compared to other pure melee types (rogues and warriors).<br>
<br>
Boy, I'll bet this is unexpected.  Melee classes seem at a glance fairly well-balanced, at least against each other.  Warriors do melee damage and tanking -- getting opponents off of other people who deal more damage or otherwise get themselves hated.  Rogues do not take damage well, however deal damage exceptionally.  Under the right circumstances, rogues can outdamage any other fighting class.  Monks in theory land somewhere in the middle, with better damage than warriors, better tanking than rogues, as well as some other abilities and drawbacks that spice up the package a bit.<br>
<br>
So, what is the deal?  Well, it ends up that many of the best weapons introduced in Kunark are usable by either monks or warriors (think Jade Mace).  The weapons are heavy enough that monks will typically have to sacrifice AC to wield them (not a problem for warriors).  Furthermore, high warrior skill caps in 1HB, DA, and DW, combined with higher strength on warriors, makes a warrior arguably as good as a monk in the damage-dealing arena.<br>
<br>
Okay, monks can pull though, right?  Well, this is another point where there's some uncertainty about the monk class.  Verant's spokesman, Abashi, has stated on at least a few occasions that the use of FD skill to pull was not intended, and has furthermore implied that this was a tactic Verant was actively working to squelch.  Changes to this ability in the past by Verant (actually, mainly aimed at necromancers using an overly effective tactic against Nagafen) have already done a good job of pooching us.  The newest dungeon, The Hole, has changes to creature behavior that makes feign pulling impossible by most accounts.<br>
<br>
No conclusion to be drawn here, just general dread that my main character will not be pulling his weight in a fight.<br>
<br>
So, what do people think about this? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/usanosuske.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sanosuske</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/13/00 12:14:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   No class envy here yet, but depends on abashi</span><hr size=1> Let me start out by saying I love being a monk. It is in my humble opinion one of the most fun classes to play. I like goin into a fight in my crescent gi and whoopin arse next to a warrior who &quot;wont wear any chestplate that has less than 35 AC&quot; and cant taunt off me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Rouge damage can be better than mine, (though most anywhere near my lvl are not) but only if certain criteria are met. I think the monk class has a solid role in a party as melee damage source. Note: I dont say tanking <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  My only concern for the class is Abashi's disappoval of Fiegn pulling. If i had not had more pressing matters at hand i wouldve been at this EQ gathering to ask him in person what he has against monks being needed for a party/raid to be most effective. Would he do this to other classes? Imagine that he gets tired of Enchanters been needed and nerfs clarity, no, no, that would NEVER happen. Bah i need to stop writing soon before this Abashi thing angers me. I just cant understand how he can justify the whole rediculous &quot;necro res&quot; spell and then turn around and take FD pulling from monks.<br>
